# Components
- Strike
	- The plane of the fault iself
	- Occurs at a particular angle
- Dip
	- The angle of inclination of the surface of a rock unit measured from a horizontal plane.
- Footwall
	- The wall that is below the fault line
- Hanging wall
	- The wall that is above the fault line

# Types

## Dip-slip faults

#### Types
- Normal fault
	- Hanging wall slides down the slope of the footwall
	- Divergent plate boundaries
- Reverse fault
	- Hanging wall is pushed up the slope of the footwall 
	- Convergent plate boundaries
- Thrust fault
	- Low-angled (<45) reverse fault
- Detachment fault
	- Low-angled (<45) normal fault


## Strike-slip faults

- Faults that move parallel to the strike of the fault
- Typically have 90* dip angle
- 2 types:
	- Left lateral
		- Opposite block moves to observer's left
	- Right-lateral
		- Opposite block moves to observer's right

## Oblique-slip faults

- Combination of dip-slip and strike-slip
- Vertical and horizontal movement
- Most common
